Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.12,0:00:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and Luise thought \Nthey might be seeing a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.29,0:00:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Father and mother finally held \Nthe wedding ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.45,0:00:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting now, as the family of four, \Nthey can live happily together.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.84,0:00:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The long-awaited days \Nof limitless happiness had finally started.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.37,0:00:30.38,Sign,,0,0,135,,{\c&HD6F9FA&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 29 \N {\fs35} Our First Family Trip {初めての家族旅行} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.32,0:00:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Modern day Vienna was granted \Nthe capital city status in the twelfth century. {totonou is "to be ready; to be prepared; to be arranged" and I honestly don't know what she means, but in this joke of an episode, I can't be bothered; wiki has it "1155\NHenry II, Duke of Austria appoints Vienna as capital city[clarification needed].[2]\NSchottenstift founded.\N1160 – St. Stephen's Cathedral built." so I'd assume this is what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was around the time \Nwhen St. Stephen's Cathedral was completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.25,0:00:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, Luise, what was the year when Wenia \Nwas renamed into modern day Vienna? {I really hope it's what they refer to, even if this shit is made up and there's no exact date when it was renamed, also it's not even the name of the city, just the hungarian way of denoting the area: https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geschichte_Wiens#Etymologie although may be Vveniam or smt}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.66,0:00:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.67,0:00:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,1030 AD!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.10,0:00:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, correct! {correct answer; right solution; correct interpretation}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.90,0:00:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.72,0:00:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Studying hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.99,0:00:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're having a social studies​ test next week. {why are they learning history? fuck if I know}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.34,0:01:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.74,0:01:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This all is so tiresome.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.08,0:01:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And what fine weather! \NI'd rather be playing outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.53,0:01:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? A trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.59,0:01:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Destination is my uncle's villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.20,0:01:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle's villa?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.75,0:01:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Last time I've been there some years ago, \NI left my important bag in his custody. {to leave (in someone's keeping); to put (in someone's care); to place (in someone's custody); to entrust (someone) with; to deposit}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.33,0:01:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I suddenly remembered it, \Nand rather than going to pick it up alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.46,0:01:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Going as a family of four!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.87,0:01:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. A good occasion for our first family trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wonderful place, \Nembraced by the nature itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.84,0:01:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Our first...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.84,0:01:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...Family trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.21,0:01:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sublime! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.58,0:01:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll also try to wrap up \Nthat manuscript I'm working on until tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.23,0:01:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! We depart today! \NRight away, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.90,0:01:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Today? Right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.89,0:01:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as you conceive something fun, \Nrealize it immediately, before it becomes boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.66,0:01:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, look at this - the tickets!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.43,0:01:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad sure is quick tempered!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.57,0:01:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he is {\i1}our{\i0} dad, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.23,0:02:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But say, if we show up so suddenly, \Nare you sure we won't bother your uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.47,0:02:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry about that. \NI had already telegraphed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.84,0:02:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it's so inopportune. \NI only have two days left until the manuscript deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.34,0:02:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, how should we prepare for the test?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.38,0:02:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.25,0:02:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For a bunch of bright Frauleins such as you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.32,0:02:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,even cramming it while on the train, \Nor upon arriving to the villa, would pose no complication.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.47,0:02:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.32,0:02:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... I don't really know... {unsure, maybe "we can't do"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.99,0:02:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Not going..?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.10,0:02:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I also support prioritizing the fun over anything else!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.03,0:02:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now come on, let's have a break, Lotte, mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.77,0:02:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that settled. \NNow, let's hurry, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.07,0:02:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You got ten minutes to pack. \NWe don't want to miss the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.07,0:02:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.06,0:02:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do you say? \NShouldn't we start packing, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.73,0:02:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.75,0:03:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I love this trip already!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.52,0:03:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey-hey, Luise. \NIt's dangerous to lean out so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, look, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.38,0:03:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Breathtaking scenery!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.73,0:03:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.60,0:03:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A scenery straight out of heavens!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone needs to take a short break.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.33,0:03:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, you also forget about studying for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.71,0:03:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't I finish studying first, \Nto fully enjoy myself later?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.14,0:03:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too serious, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.13,0:03:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you who is too carefree, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't know how to enjoy yourself. {not to bring out (the effect of); to put to good use; to make use of (e.g. threats); to use (e.g. intimidation); to take advantage of (e.g. one's influence); to season (with salt, etc.); to put in of adaptability; versatility; flexibility; accommodation - unsure what exactly she means, deepl strongly insists on "inflexible"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.77,0:03:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This excessively serious Lotte is a bore!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.94,0:03:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! The grazing cows, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.87,0:03:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,True! One is yawning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.47,0:03:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this giant mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.09,0:03:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Very true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.07,0:04:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Nice air, nice weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.50,0:04:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, yes. \NBut what if it starts to rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.56,0:04:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd you say such a thing? \NI'm trying my utmost to immerse in joy here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.41,0:04:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? But I was really wondering that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.45,0:04:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're weird, Lotte. \NNot the usual you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.85,0:04:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the most usual!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.18,0:04:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! You sound mad, even just saying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you even care, \Nif I'm too serious and boring a girl anyways?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.89,0:04:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're still mad at such a trifle?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.19,0:04:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's a trifle now? {I hope its what they mean by annakoto}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.52,0:04:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,See? I said you're too serious, \Nand now you're taking it too seriously! {/I said you're ... because you were ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.66,0:04:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So what it is you want from that serious girl? \NWhy don't you stop copying her homework, then? {lit: it's thanks to that serious girl isn't it? always profiting by copying her notebook - I assume she means "you only do homework by copying mine"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.06,0:04:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to make do without it! \NNot the end of the world. {unsure if she means "I'll do without it,  it's no big deal; it's nothing to fret about; it's not like it's the end of the world" or she means "stop it already won't you, nothing bad happened" or "why do you mind it, you don't lose nothing" something else}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.63,0:04:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow-wow, what's this all about, you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.35,0:04:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.11,0:04:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:04:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The bus is leaving! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.58,0:05:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's put this off until we're home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.21,0:05:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.17,0:05:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! I forgot. \NThe manuscript is with you, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.98,0:05:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You took it away earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.18,0:05:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.34,0:05:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.13,0:05:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, we need to leave now, \Nare you riding?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.23,0:05:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry, you can leave without us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.43,0:05:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Found it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.83,0:05:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.99,0:05:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Left it in train, after all. \NI'll go try looking for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.79,0:05:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, the train left already.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.96,0:05:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, my bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.50,0:05:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I get myself out of this now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.03,0:05:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, just remembered!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.37,0:05:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here, in your pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.64,0:06:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.40,0:06:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.74,0:06:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, aren't you glad?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.67,0:06:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, why did you have to do this... {/you're unbearable, honey}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.81,0:06:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have forgotten to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.59,0:06:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Oh no! The bus!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.66,0:06:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Gone already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.03,0:06:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No big deal, not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Can just wait for the next bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.24,0:06:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was the last bus of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.71,0:06:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with everyone? Cheer up, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.89,0:06:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as we keep walking, \Na car would pass by us at some point. {lit: if we keep (walking) leisurely; aimlessly; strolling; wandering; rambling​, a car would pass us by - I don't know what he means by wandering, leave alone coming up with a good english analogy}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.94,0:06:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, we'd ask for a ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.95,0:06:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.15,0:06:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been walking for an hour already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.86,0:06:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And not a single one passed by us yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.92,0:06:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No more
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.43,0:06:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,walking for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.63,0:07:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, just one final push, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If we stop for rest now, \Nthe sun will set before we get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.37,0:07:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun would set?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.50,0:07:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still such a long way? {actually believing sub-roro here for the first time, I've no clue what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.41,0:07:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I mean, it's possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.42,0:07:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Also starving. And thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.24,0:07:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, now the rain, too! \NWhat do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.17,0:07:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.81,0:07:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, everyone. Stick close by.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.24,0:07:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we have to go through all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.31,0:07:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.13,0:07:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If only we had taken the bus...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.35,0:08:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My, you don't suppose I'm to blame for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.23,0:08:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This rain had started now \Nbecause Lotte is so irritable about boring stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.39,0:08:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You make it my fault now? \NBut you were the one who...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.86,0:08:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, people! \NWe're on our first family trip, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.60,0:08:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, with a glee! A glee!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.67,0:08:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Rain makes for perfect leisurely strolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.05,0:08:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying here would get us nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.05,0:08:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, time for one final push.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.03,0:09:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's here. My uncle's villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.87,0:09:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.15,0:09:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they got some warm milk for me to drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.62,0:09:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm showering first, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.72,0:09:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing my uncle, \NI bet he prepared a gorgeous feast for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.20,0:09:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.94,0:09:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem like anyone's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.76,0:09:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Returned to big city life until the next spring. {lit: in the city of the down - no clue what is means}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.34,0:09:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you check with him aforehand, darling?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.15,0:10:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.29,0:10:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad's telegram is here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.03,0:10:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we to do now, dad? \NThe night is almost here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.16,0:10:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've nowhere else to go. {/we can't return from here}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.92,0:10:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it seems, stopping here is our only option.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.86,0:10:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Here? How is that an option?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.72,0:10:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, but what'll you do about the lock? {/what are you doing}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.46,0:10:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Please witness, as I conquer our way in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.35,0:10:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.23,0:10:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.30,0:10:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.29,0:10:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm all good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.40,0:10:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My, that's so much like my husband. \NOne never knows what to expect from you. {/unexpectedly going to extremes}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.47,0:11:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Either way, this gives us \Nsome roof over our heads for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.61,0:11:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're staying here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.66,0:11:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Where I lay my hat is home. {you can get used to living anywhere; home is where you make it; wherever I lay my hat is home​}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.15,0:11:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that exciting, also at a night like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.38,0:11:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And this, to our first trip as a family of four!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.90,0:11:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the water drunk \Nin a place like this tastes special.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.14,0:11:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with everyone? \NIt's like you're attending a funeral.{/gloomy}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.95,0:11:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Food tastes better if you eat it happily!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.08,0:11:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I honestly would have preferred \Nto stay home and study some more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.28,0:11:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, it can't be that you're all thinking \Nabout what would have been if we didn't go on this trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.93,0:12:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, why'd you think that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.25,0:12:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just the way you always are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.44,0:12:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Acting on the spur of the moment, \Nwithout any plan at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.82,0:12:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn a bit of self-reflection, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, what? \NHear this, then! {/Just shut up and listen.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one always absorbed in work, \Nand as I take you out, you still... {unsure what's omitted here, "even in such times, what are you..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.94,0:12:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't think about children either, \Neven though they need to study.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.72,0:12:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Serious in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.14,0:12:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with being serious? \NBetter that, than being too frivolous, like Luise. {not serious; frivolous; insincere; unsteady}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.17,0:12:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, feigning an illness and skipping school \Nwhenever you have an arithmetic test.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.50,0:12:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.63,0:12:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.78,0:12:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No! That one time, I really-really had a bellyache!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.41,0:12:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want your excuses!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.09,0:12:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, and what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.19,0:12:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.29,0:12:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.96,0:12:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You went on a secret date with a young woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.16,0:13:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.03,0:13:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she misunderstood! \NIt was a business meeting!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I thought me and were always on the same side. {/I thought you're my ally}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.83,0:13:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,When facing a choice, \Nchildren always pick mother's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.83,0:13:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's the mother \Nwho prepares their dinner daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.13,0:13:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's called daily now? \NEven if I do it myself at least three times a week?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.10,0:13:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! Mom constantly brushes it off with "work" \Nand "more work," leaving all the laundry to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.08,0:13:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know those are not the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.41,0:13:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, why don't we return \Nto the question of Luise skipping school?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.69,0:13:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm telling you I didn't feign it! \NMom, now you believe it, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.19,0:13:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, did Lotte tell a lie, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.85,0:13:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't call me a teller of lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.19,0:13:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.09,0:13:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is everyone putting on a vain act today? \NEach one of you! {lit is "selfishness; egotism; egoism; (being) self-centered; without consulting; (doing) as one pleases; one's own free will​" but I don't see how they're selfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.41,0:13:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Look who's talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.53,0:13:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the one who started it. {/dad failed us}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.23,0:13:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the worst trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.90,0:13:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, I heard you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.60,0:13:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not taking you out on a trip ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.70,0:13:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No objections. \NWith that settled, I need to get my rest now. {/going to sleep already}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.44,0:13:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So will I.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.61,0:13:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.94,0:14:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Suit yourself! The wicked need rest, too. {Lit: very well, sleep/rest all you want; as much as one wants - sleep forever sounds a bit too ominous in english and idk why he'd say "rest for as long as you want" in this situation as she'd probably do so anyways}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.49,0:14:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.88,0:14:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Worst ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.75,0:14:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what's becoming of our family so soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.41,0:14:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,One is featherbrained, the other is headstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.04,0:14:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did I take a wrong turn? {/what is missing?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.75,0:14:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, why does it all have to come to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.12,0:14:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So much for our long-awaited \Nfirst ever family trip...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.53,0:14:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.30,0:14:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.79,0:14:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.94,0:14:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.23,0:14:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No... I don't have any idea... {not in the least (with neg. verb); not at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.00,0:15:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Darling, the ceiling!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.47,0:15:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A fallen tree broke right through!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.48,0:15:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.48,0:15:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and Luise are on the second floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.36,0:15:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte! Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.86,0:15:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.09,0:15:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad! Lotte is... Lotte is in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.80,0:15:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte! Lotte, are you safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.88,0:15:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte! Answer something if you're all right! Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.56,0:15:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Step back, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.77,0:15:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.54,0:15:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.89,0:15:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.69,0:15:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.15,0:15:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Floor is crumbling!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.83,0:15:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte! Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.48,0:15:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.75,0:15:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte? Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.12,0:15:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.88,0:15:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, are you okay? Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.75,0:15:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think I'm unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.52,0:15:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.19,0:15:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! I'll try to reach you now! Stand still!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.56,0:15:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.50,0:15:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Never! What'll they do \Nif something happens to you as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.53,0:16:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.10,0:16:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I said never, so it's never!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.78,0:16:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,These children don't have anyone else \Nas important to them as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.84,0:16:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.47,0:16:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Darling...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.62,0:16:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Please be careful, darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.69,0:16:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't take any chances! {/be unreasonable/risk}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.09,0:16:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.99,0:16:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Move slowly and try to reach me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.08,0:16:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't! I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.99,0:16:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.96,0:16:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, now or never! {/come}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.30,0:16:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jump with all your might!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.43,0:16:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't! I've never done anything like that! {/can't do such a thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.14,0:16:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.73,0:16:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do it for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.03,0:16:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it with all seriousness, \Nlike nobody else can do! {lit: because I apologize for saying "Serious" earlier, you can do it - HOW is her apology/revocation of serious title should avail her to jumping? FUCK if I know}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.53,0:16:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually... This seriousness of yours \Nis what I love the most about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you wouldn't discipline me, I'd... \NI'd remain a bungler for the rest of my life! {lit: if lotte doesn't to scold; to chide; to rebuke; to reprimand​ me, I only make mistakes}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So please... Please do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.86,0:16:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.07,0:17:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.01,0:17:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.91,0:17:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.17,0:17:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're alive and well!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.15,0:17:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.06,0:17:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.06,0:17:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.83,0:18:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.93,0:18:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.76,0:18:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You seen mom and dad today?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.53,0:18:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they're up already. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.51,0:18:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, mom, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.37,0:18:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.91,0:18:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.49,0:18:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.14,0:18:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.39,0:18:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The house is in shambles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.52,0:18:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... And uncle is probably \Ngoing to kill me when he finds out. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.58,0:18:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, and what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.43,0:18:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My famous bag. \NThe very one I left in my uncle's custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.64,0:18:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Still here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.84,0:18:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.48,0:18:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.45,0:18:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my treasure from the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.55,0:19:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,On this photo, they are barely a few days old!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One is acting up! {/fighting}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.56,0:19:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The other is smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.79,0:19:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We were already this way! {/just like now}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.09,0:19:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, I could show it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.56,0:19:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that why you arranged a trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.07,0:19:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The rumors were true, \Nyou really are the world's best dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.91,0:19:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my! You sure sounded mighty different yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.40,0:19:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she really?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.64,0:19:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember! {anything of the kind}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.35,0:19:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and Luise now look with hope \Ninto the distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.66,0:19:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,On the path of the Palfy family that had barely started,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.86,0:20:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,some happy, some sad - myriads \Nof the most diverse happenings are waiting for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.87,0:20:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever challenges they are bound to face,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.74,0:20:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,by combining the powers of the four, \Nthey can definitely overcome any obstacle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.11,0:20:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, those four are one family now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.95,0:20:20.79,Sign,,0,0,0,,The End
Comment: 0,0:20:20.92,0:20:20.92,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.86,0:20:30.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.39,0:20:33.85,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.85,0:20:37.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.57,0:20:40.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.70,0:20:52.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.12,0:20:55.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.88,0:20:59.42,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.42,0:21:02.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.26,0:21:05.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.84,0:21:09.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.39,0:21:13.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.94,0:21:18.09,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.64,0:21:23.29,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.29,0:21:26.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.70,0:21:30.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.33,0:21:33.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.15,0:21:37.92,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.92,0:21:41.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.20,0:21:44.81,Sign,,0,0,270,,{\c&HDBFCFE&\bord0\blur0.8\b1\fs}Thank you for sticking with it. \NYours truly, Perevodildo.
